Azure Load Balancer:
Optional Configurations You Can Do (If Needed)
While Azure handles most things automatically. 
You can customize:
1. Autoscaling Rules

Set thresholds (e.g., scale out when CPU > 70%)
Define min/max instance counts

2. Health Checks

Configure endpoints to monitor service health
Helps Azure remove unhealthy instances from rotation

3. Traffic Routing (Advanced)

Use Azure Front Door or Application Gateway for:

Geo-routing
SSL termination
Custom traffic rules
